forecast.no_outcome_scenario: Databricks continues to signal it won’t go public in 2025 and neither files a public S-1 nor posts any IPO-intent announcement on its official news page by June 30, 2025.
forecast.yes_outcome_scenario: Despite recent comments, Databricks changes course and either publicly files an S-1 or posts on its news page that it plans to go public (e.g., announcing a forthcoming IPO or a confidential submission) before July 1, 2025.
forecast.rationale:
- Evidence and baseline: As of today, the resolution criteria have not been met. The TechCrunch/Yahoo Finance item quotes the CEO saying it’s “dumb to IPO this year,” implying 2025 is off the table. With only ~6 weeks left, the status quo strongly favors No. IPO processes often take weeks to months even after a public S-1, and companies rarely pre-announce intentions on their own news page without a filing—especially after explicitly guiding against a 2025 IPO.
- Resolution mechanics matter: This question resolves Yes only on (1) a public S-1 filing or (2) an announcement on Databricks’ own news page. Press leaks or third-party reports alone won’t resolve it. That further lowers the chance because it requires Databricks’ own public action.
- Why not lower: Late-stage private companies can pivot quickly if market windows open or strategic needs (employee liquidity, secondary overhang, competitive/market signaling) become urgent. The company could also post a brief news item acknowledging a plan to go public or a confidential submission, which would satisfy the criteria without a public S-1.
- Why not higher: The CEO’s recent stance against a 2025 IPO, the legal/comms conservatism around IPOs, and the short remaining window materially constrain the odds. Also, if they were already close, we might expect preparatory signals (IR build-out, banker chatter, reporting cadence) to surface—none are noted here.
- What would move me upward: Credible reports of a confidential filing paired with Databricks signaling on its own channels; a sudden, strong IPO window (AI/software comps ripping, several successful June listings); an unexpected Databricks news post about pursuing a listing (IPO or direct listing). What would move me downward: Reinforced public statements that no 2025 IPO is planned; further market volatility; absence of any preparatory signals by mid-June.
- Research assistant summary: No additional info provided beyond the background link, which supports the CEO’s non-IPO stance for 2025.
